Volcán de Chiriquí , 25-4000 ft , Champion – 1 male ( lectotype ) ( BMNH ); Canal Zone, Barro Colorado Island, 24 - 25 June 1968 (coll. O.J. Sexton) - 1 male ( UMMZ ); CO- LOMBIA: Dept. Magdalena , Minca, elev. 610 m , - 1 male ( ANSP ).

Male 10th tergite with deep incision on posterior margin, resulting in two large, pointed lobes (note: Fig. 22 H shows the lobes from above, when the pointed ends of the lobes cannot be seen). Male cercus relatively slender, cylindrical, with small, blunt dorsal spine; apex of cercus blunt (
Fig. 22I
). Titillators flat, squamose, somewhat narrowed towards their apices ( Fig. 23 D). Male subgenital plate with distinct ventral keel and deep triangular incision apically; female subgenital plate broadly triangular, with small, triangular incision at apex.

